Is it easy for Germany to combine its close ties with Israel and the US on the one hand and the position of the most important partner in the EU on the other?
I think that's what makes it so difficult for the Germans.
Of course, Germans would be a little easier if there was a single, consistent European policy, but now it isn't.
They are therefore unable to take a broader approach and are forced to act instead on the basis of their own vision of the situation.
That's what they do with the euro.
I think that in the future Germany will take the lead in developing a common European position.
It is clear that it is not easy for Germany, at least because of ties with Israel.
This subject has always been tickling.
