During the cross-examination at the pre-trial hearing in Fort Meida, Maryland, the military prosecutor, Major Ashden Fein, stated that the weekly visits to Manning by the prison administration during the nine months of his detention in Quantico, Virginia, did not contain complaints of ill-treatment.
The cross-examination in the context of the defence ' s application for the termination of Manning ' s case, on the grounds that the conditions of his detention were cruel and in themselves sufficient punishment, was conducted the day after Manning stated that he had intended to commit suicide while in detention.
