WikiLeaks has not confirmed that Manning was the source of the information.
During the Friday hearing, Prosecutor Fein, together with Manning, reviewed the reports that had been completed following the visits of the Administration to Manning during his stay in Quantico prison, where he was under strict conditions of detention from July 2010 to April 2011.
During the visits, prison officials asked Manning questions and recorded his answers.
When Prosecutor Fein asked about the reports on Friday, Manning admitted that he assessed the treatment of himself by the prison administration as "best" and the general conditions of detention as "very professionally organized."
The reports examined do not contain complaints of ill-treatment, despite Manning ' s direct request for conditions of detention, Fein claims.
Manning replied that he had expressed his oral concern about those problems and that the officials who visited him had discussed those problems and had stated that they would do so but had not recorded it in writing.
