The military judge, Colonel Denis Linde, also asked Manning why he had not complained about his ill-treatment in January 2011 during a meeting of the commission dealing with the suicidal intentions he had expressed in writing a few months earlier.
Manning replied that during that meeting, he wanted to ensure that he was removed from the regime of injury prevention and reduced conditions of detention.
Members of the military leadership explained that the limited regime of detention - lower than the regime of surveillance to prevent suicide - had been introduced to protect the prisoner and to protect others.
